<emphasis bold="true" box="[999,1034,1037,1063]" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">A8</emphasis>
): 
<taxonomicName authority="Meade, 1891" authorityName="Meade" authorityYear="1891" box="[1060,1399,1037,1063]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Mydaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis box="[1060,1236,1037,1063]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">Mydaea affinis</emphasis>
Meade, 1891
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[199,303,1072,1099]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="29.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[209,1380,270,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-59@29.[208,1380,264,1907]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="Fig. 15. ♀♀ of Muscidae Latreille, 1802. A. Myospila bimaculata (Macquart, 1834), detail of wing showing CS1–3, dorsal view. B. Mydaea ancilla (Meigen, 1826), detail of wing showing CS1–3, dorsal view. C. M. affinis Meade, 1891, detail of wing showing CS1–3, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6784161" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6784161/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">Fig. 15C</figureCitation>
), some 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Robineau-Desvoidy" authorityYear="1830" box="[386,540,1072,1098]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Mydaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="humeralis">
<emphasis box="[386,540,1072,1098]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">M. humeralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Stein, 1893)" baseAuthorityName="Stein" baseAuthorityYear="1893" box="[555,857,1072,1099]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Mydaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nebulosa">
<emphasis box="[555,698,1072,1098]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">M. nebulosa</emphasis>
(Stein, 1893)
</taxonomicName>
, some 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ringdahl" authorityYear="1924" box="[931,1077,1073,1099]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Potamia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="setifemur">
<emphasis box="[931,1077,1073,1099]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">M. setifemur</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Ringdahl, 1928" authorityName="Ringdahl" authorityYear="1928" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Mydaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sootryeni">
<emphasis box="[1130,1276,1073,1098]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">M. sootryeni</emphasis>
Ringdahl, 1928
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[189,693,1173,1199]" box="[189,693,1173,1199]" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">
<emphasis box="[189,199,1174,1199]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">•</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Schnabl, 1889" authorityName="Schnabl" authorityYear="1889" box="[214,528,1173,1199]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Hebecnema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[214,352,1173,1199]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">Hebecnema</emphasis>
Schnabl, 1889
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[544,685,1173,1199]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="31.[189,232,1926,1952]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,268,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-60@31.[203,1385,265,1908]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Fig. 16. ♀♀ of Muscidae Latreille, 1802. A. Hebecnema umbratica (Meigen, 1826), detail of wing showing CS1–3, dorsal view. B. H. nigricolor (Fallén, 1825), detail of wing showing CS1–3, dorsal view. C. Gymnodia subtilis (Stein, 1909), detail of wing showing CS1–3, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6784163" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6784163/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">Fig. 16A–B</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[189,1399,1219,1352]" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">
Most species examined, e.g., 
<taxonomicName authority="(Meigen, 1826)" baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1826" box="[554,915,1219,1246]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Hebecnema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="umbratica">
<emphasis box="[554,575,1220,1245]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[595,716,1220,1246]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">umbratica</emphasis>
(Meigen, 1826)
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[937,1050,1219,1246]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="31.[189,232,1926,1952]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,268,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-60@31.[203,1385,265,1908]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Fig. 16. ♀♀ of Muscidae Latreille, 1802. A. Hebecnema umbratica (Meigen, 1826), detail of wing showing CS1–3, dorsal view. B. H. nigricolor (Fallén, 1825), detail of wing showing CS1–3, dorsal view. C. Gymnodia subtilis (Stein, 1909), detail of wing showing CS1–3, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6784163" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6784163/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">Fig. 16A</figureCitation>
), have the prevalent muscid state 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[253,289,1255,1281]" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">A4</emphasis>
, but 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fallen, 1825)" baseAuthorityName="Fallen" baseAuthorityYear="1825" box="[355,692,1255,1282]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Hebecnema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigricolor">
<emphasis box="[355,376,1256,1281]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[394,513,1255,1281]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">nigricolor</emphasis>
(Fallén, 1825)
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[712,822,1255,1281]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="31.[189,232,1926,1952]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,268,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-60@31.[203,1385,265,1908]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Fig. 16. ♀♀ of Muscidae Latreille, 1802. A. Hebecnema umbratica (Meigen, 1826), detail of wing showing CS1–3, dorsal view. B. H. nigricolor (Fallén, 1825), detail of wing showing CS1–3, dorsal view. C. Gymnodia subtilis (Stein, 1909), detail of wing showing CS1–3, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6784163" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6784163/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">Fig. 16B</figureCitation>
), as first noticed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Michelsen V." box="[1074,1288,1255,1281]" pageId="28" pageNumber="122" pagination="332 - 348" refId="ref15079" refString="Michelsen V. 2019. Macaronesian Muscidae (Diptera). I. The genus Hebecnema Schnabl with description of a new Canarian endemic species and a review of the European fauna. Zootaxa 4706 (2): 332 - 348. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4706.2.7" type="journal article" year="2019">Michelsen (2019)</bibRefCitation>
, and one unidentified species from 
<collectingCountry box="[494,599,1290,1316]" name="Tanzania" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
deviate by having dorsal setulae on the basal two-thirds or more of CS3, and sometimes among females even some irregular dorsal setulae on CS2 (state 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1196,1231,1325,1351]" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">A7</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[189,499,1398,1424]" box="[189,499,1398,1424]" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">
<emphasis box="[189,199,1399,1424]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">•</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Wulp, 1896" authorityName="Wulp" authorityYear="1896" box="[214,499,1398,1424]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Hemichlora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[214,354,1398,1424]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">Hemichlora</emphasis>
Wulp, 1896
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[189,1399,1445,1506]" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">
The only included species, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Walker, 1861)" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1861" box="[531,993,1445,1471]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Hemichlora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scordalus">
<emphasis box="[531,796,1445,1471]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">Hemichlora scordalus</emphasis>
(Walker, 1861)
</taxonomicName>
, has vein C extensively setulose dorsally (state 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[362,408,1480,1506]" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">A8)</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[189,779,1553,1579]" box="[189,779,1553,1579]" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">
<emphasis box="[189,199,1554,1579]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">•</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Robineau-Desvoidy, 1863" authorityName="Robineau-Desvoidy" authorityYear="1863" box="[214,650,1553,1579]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Gymnodia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[214,336,1553,1579]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">Gymnodia</emphasis>
Robineau-Desvoidy, 1863
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[666,771,1553,1579]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="31.[189,232,1926,1952]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,268,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-60@31.[203,1385,265,1908]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Fig. 16. ♀♀ of Muscidae Latreille, 1802. A. Hebecnema umbratica (Meigen, 1826), detail of wing showing CS1–3, dorsal view. B. H. nigricolor (Fallén, 1825), detail of wing showing CS1–3, dorsal view. C. Gymnodia subtilis (Stein, 1909), detail of wing showing CS1–3, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6784163" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6784163/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">Fig. 16C</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[189,1399,1599,1731]" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">
Most of the 12 species examined show the prevalent muscid state 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[971,1006,1599,1625]" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">A4</emphasis>
, in which vein C is bare dorsally and extensively setulose ventrally, but a ventrally bare CS1 (state 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[969,1005,1634,1660]" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">A3</emphasis>
) was found in 
<taxonomicName authority="(Stein, 1909)" baseAuthorityName="Stein" baseAuthorityYear="1909" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Gymnodia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subtilis">
<emphasis box="[1184,1399,1635,1661]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">Gymnodia subtilis</emphasis>
(Stein, 1909)
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[363,470,1670,1696]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="31.[189,232,1926,1952]" captionTargetBox="[203,1385,268,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-60@31.[203,1385,265,1908]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Fig. 16. ♀♀ of Muscidae Latreille, 1802. A. Hebecnema umbratica (Meigen, 1826), detail of wing showing CS1–3, dorsal view. B. H. nigricolor (Fallén, 1825), detail of wing showing CS1–3, dorsal view. C. Gymnodia subtilis (Stein, 1909), detail of wing showing CS1–3, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6784163" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6784163/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">Fig. 16C</figureCitation>
) and a few other small-sized, unidentified 
<taxonomicName box="[987,1160,1670,1696]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Gymnodia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[987,1109,1670,1696]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="122">Gymnodia</emphasis>
spp
</taxonomicName>
of Afrotropical and Oriental origin.
</paragraph>
